"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851644","Home Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>In accordance with arrangements introduced in 2016, the police write to the GPs of those who apply for a firearms licence to seek relevant information regarding the applicant’s health before the licence is issued. We do not collect statistics on the number of certificates that have been granted without the applicant’s GP having participated in the process. However, reports from police forces and firearms licence applicants indicate that the participation rates amongst GPs are variable. We have been in discussions with the police, medical bodies and shooting representatives about how greater consistency can be achieved.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","130410","2018-03-07T16:07:13.223Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851644/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851644/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851644/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-28","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what estimate her Department has made of the number of shotgun and firearms certificates that have been granted where the applicant's doctor has not participated in the licensing process in the last three years.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","130407"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851645","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Department does not hold this information. The system is run by the Home Office.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-08T15:12:00.54Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851645/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851645/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851645/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-28","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what information his Department holds on the number of GPs who are co-operating with the system of placing a marker on the medical notes of a person who has shotgun and firearm certificates.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","130408"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851646","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-08","<p>All members of the Armed Forces receive training on international humanitarian law which includes law relating to sexual violence in conflict as part of their pre-deployment training. Additionally, the Armed Forces have over 40 gender advisers who are trained to advise on appropriate responses to sexual violence in conflict.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-08T15:00:23.273Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851646/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851646/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851646/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Armed Conflict: Sexual Offences","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what training members of the armed forces receive in respect of the initiative on the prevention of sexual violence in conflict.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130409"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851647","Home Office","false","2018-03-07","<p>In accordance with arrangements introduced in 2016, the police write to the GPs of those who apply for a firearms licence to seek relevant information regarding the applicant’s health before the licence is issued. We do not collect statistics on the number of certificates that have been granted without the applicant’s GP having participated in the process. However, reports from police forces and firearms licence applicants indicate that the participation rates amongst GPs are variable. We have been in discussions with the police, medical bodies and shooting representatives about how greater consistency can be achieved.</p>","Ruislip, Northwood and Pinner","Mr Nick Hurd","130407","2018-03-07T16:07:13.27Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851647/answer","Biography information for Mr Nick Hurd","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851647/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851647/answer",,,,,"1","Home Office","Home Office","2018-02-28","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for the Home Department, what information her Department holds on the number of GPs in each police constabulary area who are not participating in the firearms licensing process.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","130410"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851648","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains engaged with Babcock to understand its Defence Support Group plans, including the location of its future operations. As Babcock is a key supplier to the Department, the issue has been raised at regular meetings between senior officials and the company.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","130414","2018-03-07T15:48:35.577Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851648/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851648/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851648/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Babcock International: Stirling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions he has had with Babcock Defence Support Group on the future use of the Forthside estate in Stirling.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130411"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851649","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-08","<p>The Department has made no assessment on this issue.</p>","Winchester","Steve Brine",,"2018-03-08T15:12:55.61Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851649/answer","Biography information for Steve Brine","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851649/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851649/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-28","Firearms: Licensing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, what recent assessment he has made of the level of charges that GPs pass on to applicants for medical reports required for new or renewed shotgun and firearms certificates.","false","Biography information for Mr Gavin Shuker","Luton South","Mr Gavin Shuker","130412"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851650","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-08","<p>An initial meeting was held between Ministry of Defence representatives and Stirling Council officials on 8 June 2010. Subsequent meetings have taken place during 2011-12, in April 2016 and more recently in January 2017.</p>","Bournemouth East","Mr Tobias Ellwood",,"2018-03-08T15:45:57.877Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851650/answer","Biography information for Mr Tobias Ellwood","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851650/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851650/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Ministry of Defence: Stirling","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what recent discussions have taken place between his Department and Stirling Council on the future use of his Department's Forthside estate in Stirling.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130413"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851651","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-07","<p>The Ministry of Defence remains engaged with Babcock to understand its Defence Support Group plans, including the location of its future operations. As Babcock is a key supplier to the Department, the issue has been raised at regular meetings between senior officials and the company.</p>","Aberconwy","Guto Bebb","130411","2018-03-07T15:48:35.64Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851651/answer","Biography information for Guto Bebb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851651/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851651/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Babcock International: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, what discussions have taken place between his Department and Babcock DSG on (a) the future of that company's operations in Scotland and (b) the location of a mobile base of operation in Scotland.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130414"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851652","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-08","<p>During the course of the Review of Modern Working Practices, the panel held events across the UK including in Wales and Northern Ireland. Unfortunately due to the General Election in 2017, the scheduled event for Scotland was cancelled. Officials in the Department speak regularly to their counterparts in the Devolved Administrations and we look forward to engaging with them through the further work set out in the Government response to the Review of Modern Working Practices.</p>","Burton","Andrew Griffiths",,"2018-03-08T15:24:12.927Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851652/answer","Biography information for Andrew Griffiths","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851652/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851652/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-28","Modern Working Practices Review","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has held with the devolved administrations on the Government's response to the Matthew Taylor review of modern working practices; and what the outcomes of those discussions were.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130415"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851653","Department for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","false","2018-03-08","<p>As part of our ambitious Industrial Strategy, BEIS will provide up to £13m to fund &quot;Be the Business&quot;, a charity set up by the Productivity Leadership Group to help firms become more productive. Be the Business is currently in set-up phase. BEIS officials will arrange to meet with their Scottish Government counterparts and Be the Business to discuss how its privately and publicly funded activities can benefit Scottish business, within devolved arrangements.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2018-03-08T16:07:46.607Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851653/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851653/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851653/answer",,,,,"201","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy","2018-02-28","Productivity Leadership Group: Scotland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Business, Energy and Industrial Strategy, what discussions his Department has had with the Scottish Government on (a) the Productivity Leadership Group and (b) the scope of that group's activities with Scottish businesses.","false","Biography information for Stephen Kerr","Stirling","Stephen Kerr","130416"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851654","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-09","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost. This is because the information is held locally by individual lead agencies within the 42 MAPPA areas and is not collated centrally.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-09T14:19:38.433Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851654/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851654/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851654/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-28","Offenders: Foreign Nationals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many foreign national offenders are subject to multi-agency public protection arrangements.","false","Biography information for Priti Patel","Witham","Priti Patel","130417"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851655","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-05","<p>As one of the 16 historic Sending States to the United Nations Command in Korea, the UK routinely contributes a small number of staff officers to annual joint United States - Republic of Korea exercises. These include Exercise KEY RESOLVE, normally held in the spring, and Exercise ULCHI FREEDOM GUARDIAN, held in late summer.</p><p>These exercises are in accordance with the UK's role in upholding the Korean Armistice Agreement, are defensive in nature and demonstrate our commitment to supporting peace and stability on the peninsula. We will continue to provide support to these exercises.</p><p>In addition, the deployment of Royal Navy ships to the region during 2018 will see participation in other joint exercises with partners such as the Republic of Korea, Japan and the United States.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-05T17:49:48.71Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851655/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851655/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851655/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","South Korea: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, which joint exercises with South Korea he plans the UK to participate in over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130418"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851656","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-15","<p>There are currently 82 exercises planned to have UK and US participation (and in some cases, other coalition countries) between March 2018 and March 2020. These are laid out in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>We are unable to provide specific figures for numbers of personnel participating as those details are not finalised until closer to the date of the exercise.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","130422","2018-03-15T16:21:54.75Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851656/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851656/answer","Exercise Extract for US Involment..docx","Exercise Extract for US Involment..docx","EX Planning Name (EPN)","EX Planning Name (EPN)","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851656/answer","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851656/answer/previousversion/44810","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","USA: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, which joint exercises with the US he plans the UK to participate in over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130419"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851657","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-05","<p>We are developing plans for Royal Navy ships to participate in bilateral exercises with the Japanese Maritime Self-Defense Force during their respective deployments to East Asia in 2018.</p><p>We also plan to participate in a land-based exercise in Japan in October 2018 with elements of the Japanese Ground Self-Defense Force.</p><p>These exercises deliver on a 2017 commitment made by the UK and Japanese Prime Ministers to conduct joint training and exercises.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-05T17:48:51.777Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851657/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851657/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851657/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Japan: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, which joint exercises with Japan he plans the UK to participate in over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130420"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851658","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-05","<p>In line with our participation in recent years, the number of personnel currently expected to participate in UN Command-led Exercise KEY RESOLVE later this spring are:</p><p>Army 44</p><p>Royal Navy 6</p><p>Royal Air Force 6</p><p>No decisions on the number of personnel planned to participate in future joint exercises with the Republic of Korea over the next two years have been taken. In accordance with the UK's role in upholding the Korean Armistice Agreement, we will continue to provide support to routine, defensive UN Command-led exercises.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-05T17:50:52.53Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851658/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851658/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851658/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","South Korea: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, how many personnel from the (a) Army, (b) Royal Navy and (c) Royal Air Force are planned to participate in joint exercises with South Korea over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130421"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851659","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-15","<p>There are currently 82 exercises planned to have UK and US participation (and in some cases, other coalition countries) between March 2018 and March 2020. These are laid out in the attached table.</p><p> </p><p>We are unable to provide specific figures for numbers of personnel participating as those details are not finalised until closer to the date of the exercise.</p><p> </p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","130419","2018-03-15T16:21:54.813Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851659/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851659/answer","Exercise Extract for US Involment..docx","Exercise Extract for US Involment..docx","EX Planning Name (EPN)","EX Planning Name (EPN)","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851659/answer","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851659/answer/previousversion/44808","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","USA: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, how many personnel from the (a) Army, (b) Royal Navy and (c) Royal Air Force are planned to participate in joint exercises with the US over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130422"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851660","Ministry of Defence","false","2018-03-07","<p>Personnel from HMS SUTHERLAND and HMS ARGYLL will also take part in joint exercises with the Japanese Maritime Self-Defense Force during their respective deployments to East Asia in 2018.</p><p>Around 45 Army personnel will take part in a land-based exercise in Japan in October 2018 with elements of the Japanese Ground Self-Defense Force</p><p>These exercises deliver on a 2017 commitment made by the UK and Japanese Prime Ministers to conduct joint training and exercises.</p>","Milton Keynes North","Mark Lancaster",,"2018-03-07T15:52:49.797Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851660/answer","Biography information for Mark Lancaster","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851660/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851660/answer",,,,,"11","Defence","Defence","2018-02-28","Japan: Joint Exercises","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Defence, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2018 to Question 123796, how many personnel from the (a) Army, (b) Royal Navy and (c) Royal Air Force are planned to participate in joint exercises with Japan over the next two years.","false","Biography information for Nia Griffith","Llanelli","Nia Griffith","130423"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851661","Department of Health and Social Care","false","2018-03-08","<p>This information is not available in the format requested. NHS England publishes quarterly performance data on the number of last minute elective operations cancelled for non-clinical reasons.</p><p> </p><p>This can be accessed via NHS England’s statistical work areas webpage at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/cancelled-elective-operations/cancelled-ops-data/" target="_blank">https://www.england.nhs.uk/statistics/statistical-work-areas/cancelled-elective-operations/cancelled-ops-data/</a></p><p> </p><p>The National Emergency Pressures Panel (NEPP) met on 2 January 2018 and recommended that non-urgent operations be deferred until 31 January 2018 to increase capacity for emergency cases. NEPP’s recommendations to trusts were clear that cancer operations and procedures where deferral would lead to a deterioration in the patient’s condition were not in scope and should continue as planned.</p><p> </p><p>NHS England and NHS Improvement will undertake a review of the arrangements and interventions undertaken this winter, including the recommendations issued by NEPP on the deferment of patients’ routine elective treatment. For those patients who have not had new appointments, cancelled operations should be rescheduled at the earliest opportunity, taking into account patients’ clinical need.</p>","North East Cambridgeshire","Stephen Barclay",,"2018-03-08T17:02:04.617Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851661/answer","Biography information for Stephen Barclay","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851661/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851661/answer",,,,,"17","Health and Social Care","Health and Social Care","2018-02-28","Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health and Social Care, how many operations at Wirral University Teaching Hospital NHS Foundation Trust have been (a) postponed and (b) cancelled in the most recent three months for which data is available.","false","Biography information for Frank Field","Birkenhead","Frank Field","130424"
