"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851731","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-09","<p>The requested information is not stored centrally. The Ministry of Justice would be required to manually check the monthly scorecards of all contracts held with Amey to determine what proportion of key performance indicators were met. The information requested could therefore only be obtained at disproportionate cost</p><p><br> The MoJ closely monitors Private providers performance and will not hesitate to act where standards fall short. It is important to recognise that providers achieve the majority of their contractual targets.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-09T14:12:28.523Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851731/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851731/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851731/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-28","Ministry of Justice: Amey","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, what proportion of key performance indicators were met by Amey in contracts that company held with his Department in each year since the first contract was signed.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","130494"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851732","Ministry of Justice","false","2018-03-09","<p>This information is not held centrally.</p><p> </p><p>Information about the volumes and outcomes of appeals to the First-tier Tribunal (Social Security and Child Support) is published at: www.gov.uk/government/collections/tribunals-statistics.</p><p> </p><p>The latest statistics can be viewed at: www.gov.uk/government/statistics/tribunals-and-gender-recognition-certificate-statistics-quarterly-july-to-september-2017.</p>","Penrith and The Border","Rory Stewart",,"2018-03-09T14:05:21.807Z",,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851732/answer","Biography information for Rory Stewart","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851732/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/851732/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2018-02-28","Disability Living Allowance: Appeals","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many people have won an appeal against the withdrawal of their disability living allowance at a tribunal in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Richard Burgon","Leeds East","Richard Burgon","130495"
